<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1435,151,294]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,220,152,178]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Note:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ridley" authorityYear="1915" box="[250,484,151,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotifolia">
<emphasis box="[250,484,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Justicia remotifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by having coriaceous leaves and lax paniculate inflorescences with two small ovate leaves at the base of peduncle. This species is found only in 
<collectingRegion box="[1114,1264,190,216]" country="Thailand" name="Chaiyaphum" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Chaiyaphum</collectingRegion>
(north-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[151,257,229,255]" name="Thailand" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">Thailand</collectingCountry>
) and in the Malay Peninsula. The original description of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Imlay" authorityYear="1939" box="[920,1060,228,254]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oligantha">
<emphasis box="[920,1060,228,254]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">J. oligantha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
matches very well with the 
<typeStatus box="[1385,1435,229,255]" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ridley" authorityYear="1915" box="[182,339,267,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Acanthaceae" genus="Justicia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Lamiales" pageId="5" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="remotifolia">
<emphasis box="[182,339,267,293]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="48">J. remotifolia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, the former is placed as a synonym of the latter.
</paragraph>
